@cindex ARM, The
CC-Mode is a GNU Emacs package written entirely in Emacs Lisp.  It is
used to edit C and C++ code and provides customizable indentation
styles and other conveniences for writing, using, and maintaining C
and C++ programs.  CC-Mode supports both ANSI-C style prototyped
headers and K&R style function declarations.  CC-Mode also supports
C++ code, using the Annotated C++ Reference Manual (a.k.a. @dfn{The
ARM}) as a standard. @xref{References}.

